Package: r-other-reaktanz-korpus
Architecture: all
Section: math
Depends: r-base (>= 2.15.0)
Description: GNU R package: A set of tools to analyze texts. Includes, amongst others, functions for automatic language detection,
 hyphenation, several indices of lexical diversity (e.g., type token ratio, HD-D/vocd-D, MTLD) and readability (e.g., Flesch, SMOG,
 LIX, Dale-Chall). Basic import functions for language corpora are also provided, to enable frequency analyses (supports Celex and
 Leipzig Corpora Collection file formats).  #' Note: For full functionality a local installation of TreeTagger is recommended.  Be
 encouraged to send feedback to the author(s)!
Homepage: http://reaktanz.de/?c=hacking&s=koRpus
